==English==

===Verb===
'''[[fall]] [[off]] the [[wagon]]'''

# {{idiom}} To [[cease]] or [[fail]] at a regimen of self-improvement or [[reform]]; to [[lapse]] back into an old [[habit]] or [[addiction]].
#:''Though he '''fell off the wagon''' several times, he eventually succeeded in quitting.''

